  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "TL has revolutionized image recognition by enabling models trained on large datasets like ImageNet (Krizhevsky et al. 2012) to be adapted for specific tasks with limited data (Faes et al. 2019; Raina et al. 2007; Agarwal et al. 2021; Ribani and Marengoni 2019; Fig. 5 The transfer learning approach, showing the adaptation of a pre-trained DL model to a new task, where initial layers retain basic features and later layers are fine-tuned, thereby enhancing computational efficiency Alzubaidi et al. 2021).",
    "This approach alleviates the need for extensive labeled datasets.",
    "Similarly, TL has advanced natural language processing (NLP) with models like BERT (Tenney et al. 2019) and GPT (Nath et al. 2022), which, when fine-tuned, excel in tasks such as sentiment analysis (Araci 2019), translation (Zoph et al. 2016), and question-answering (Dai et al. 2008; Aji et al. 2020).",
    "In microfossil classification, TL enables accurate and efficient classification by leveraging pre-trained models (Wang et al. 2022; Pires de Lima et al. 2020; Yu et al. 2023; Salehi et al. 2023).",
    "However, TL's effectiveness depends on the relevance of the pre-trained model to the task (Langnickel and Fluck 2021; Soltan et al. 2021)."
  ],
